\displaystyle\int_{1}^{x} \frac{\pi(t)}{t^2} dt
x
O\left(\frac{x}{\log x}\right).
\int_1^x \frac{\pi(t)}{t}dt = \int_1^x \frac{1}{\log t}dt+O\left(\int_1^x \frac{1}{\log^2 t}dt\right)
=\frac{x}{\log x}+O\left(\frac{x}{\log^2 x}\right).
\text{li}(x)=\int_2^x \frac{1}{\log t}dt
\int_1^x \frac{\pi(t)}{t} dt=\sum_{p\leq x} \log(x/p).
\sum_{p\leq x} \log x =\log x \text{li}(x)+O\left(xe^{-c\sqrt{\log x}}\right)
\sum_{p\leq x} \log p = \theta(x)=x+O\left(xe^{-c\sqrt{\log x}}\right).
\int_1^x \frac{\pi(t)}{t} dt=\log x \text{li}(x)-x +O\left(xe^{-c\sqrt{\log x}}\right)
\int_1^x \frac{\pi(t)}{t} dt=\frac{x}{\log x}+\frac{2x}{\log^2 x}+\cdots .
